class Solution {
    public int minInsertions(String s) {
        int count = 0, open = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '(') {
                open++;
            } else {
                if (open == 0) count++;
                else open--;
                if (count % 2 == 1) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
        }
        return count + 2 * open;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string once, maintaining a count of the minimum insertions needed and the number of open parentheses. It correctly handles cases where '(' or ')' is encountered, adjusting counts accordingly to ensure the string is balanced.
